# .context.md — Template

<!--
  Place this file in any directory to provide domain-specific context
  to AI coding agents working in that directory.

  Guidelines:
  - Keep it under 200 tokens
  - Only include information NOT derivable from reading the code
  - Focus on tribal knowledge, non-obvious constraints, and gotchas
  - Update when conventions change (treat it like code, not docs)
  - Delete sections that don't apply
-->

## Purpose

<!-- What does this directory/module do? One sentence. -->
[e.g., Handles authentication and authorization for all API endpoints]

## Key Conventions

<!-- Rules specific to this area of the codebase -->
- [e.g., All handlers must validate JWT before processing]
- [e.g., Rate limiting is handled by middleware, not individual handlers]
- [e.g., Use domain errors from pkg/errors, not raw HTTP status codes]

## Non-Obvious Constraints

<!-- Things that would surprise someone working here for the first time -->
- [e.g., The legacy auth adapter in adapters/legacy.go talks to a SOAP service — don't try to "modernize" it]
- [e.g., Session tokens have a 15-minute TTL enforced by the upstream proxy, not by this code]

## Integration Points

<!-- How this code connects to other parts of the system -->
- [e.g., Called by API middleware in src/api/middleware.go]
- [e.g., Publishes events to the auth channel via src/events/publisher.go]
- [e.g., Uses the user store in src/infra/stores/user_store.go]

## Danger Zones

<!-- Things that can go very wrong -->
- [e.g., Don't modify the token validation logic without running the full integration suite — it's caught production bugs twice]
- [e.g., The billing webhook handler has race conditions under load — see issue #423]
